Welcome to the serpentine encourager!


a) Print encouragement
b) Print flag
c) Quit

What would you like to do? (a/b/c) b

Oops! I must have misplaced the print_flag function! Check my source code!


After checking the code, there is a function called print_flag()
Adding that option to the choice b is the reccomended fix. You could also just call the function independently of the choice. Either way it prints the flag. 
I edited the file by changing it like this:


elif choice == 'b':
      #print('\nOops! I must have misplaced the print_flag function! Check my source code!\n\n')
      print_flag()
      




